ger circumnuclear star formation\nin the near future. We propose a scenario in which gas from the polar ring,\nwhich probably originated from the capture of a dwarf galaxy, is moving inwards\nand triggering an AGN, as supported by the local X-ray emission, which seems to\nbe the source of the H$_2$ 1-0 S(1) excitation. The fact that we see neither\nnear-UV nor Br$\\gamma$ emission suggests that the nascent AGN is still deeply\nburied under the optically thick dust of the polar ring.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Mar 2022 19:19:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 18 Jul 2022 17:44:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-19"}
